[[Translation:en/Manual/Stations]]
'''Stations''' are the most important part of any network. They are where [[en/Manual/Cargo]] is collected and loaded onto [[en/Manual/Vehicles]]. Each mode of transport has its own type of station:

*'''[[en/Manual/Railway station]]''' are used by trains.  The basic station layout remains the same for all types of rail.
*'''[[en/Manual/Airports]]''' are the loading and unloading points for aeroplanes. There are many types of airport including [[heliport]s for [[en/Helicopters]].
*'''[[en/Manual/Water Transport Tiles]]''' are where your ships berth.
*'''[[en/Manual/Loading Bays]]''' are where buses and lorries load and unload goods and passengers.